template:docs/atoms/au-button.title: Button
template:docs/atoms/au-button.text: Button Primary button Indicates the main action of the view (only one should be used per view). Primary button Primary button - large Primary button - icon Primary button - block Primary button - error Primary button - loading Primary button - disabled Secondary button Addon to a primary action (should not be used without the presence of a primary button). Secondary button Secondary button - large Secondary button - icon Secondary button - block Secondary button - error Secondary button - loading Secondary button - disabled Tertiary button Can be used as a standalone secondary action. Link button Link button - large Link button - block Link button - error Link button - loading Link button - disabled Properties @skin: [ secondary | tertiary ] - default is primary @size: [ large ] - makes a button larger @width: [ block ] - makes a button behave like a block element @alert: [ true ] - adds an alert state to the button @disabled: [ true ] - adds a disabled state to the button @loading: [ true ] - adds a loading state to the button Button Group Groups and spaces buttons Primary button in group Secondary button in group Large primary button in group Large secondary button in group

template:docs/atoms/au-icon.title: Icon
template:docs/atoms/au-icon.text: Icon Usage Add your icons to the public/icons folder as .svg. Make sure to export your svg's without fill or stroke colors so we can style these with CSS. Adding icons The appuniversum-symbolset is generated by svg-symbols. Run npm run icons to generate or update the symbolset. Properties @icon: pass the svg name to select the icon @size: [ medium | large ] @alignment: add [ left | right ] margin to the icon - default is none @ariaHidden: [ true | false ] - default is true Included icons add alert-triangle archive arrow-down arrow-left arrow-right arrow-up bin bold calendar check cross document documents draft export github hierarchal-back indent italic info-circle link login logout manual message nav-down nav-left nav-right nav-up nav-up-down ordered-list pencil plus-text question-circle redo renew reverse-indent search search-folder settings sitemap strikethrough switch underlined unordered-list user user-fill user-popup users
